				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$({\eta }_{T})$$\end{document} from Bi3+ to Eu3+ were 50.84% and 40.17% monitoring at 410 and 485 nm, respectively. The internal quantum efficiency of the optimized Ba9Lu2Si6O24:Bi3+, Eu3+ phosphor was calculated to be 42.6%. In addition, the configurational coordinate model was carried out to explain the energy decrease of the phonon-electron coupling effect.

